This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) as it deals with modeling events in online discussion forums, which are a form of social network. Additionally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to analyze the data, which falls under the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves natural language processing, which is a sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper's focus on predicting the arrival time of future events suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper's use of data from Reddit, which is a popular online discussion forum, suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of Cybersecurity (cs.CY).
